public interface ValueGenerator<T>
Defines a block that generates a value whenever the DataBuilder.create(gw.pl.persistence.core.Bundle) method is called.
See Also:
  • DataBuilder.set(gw.lang.reflect.IPropertyInfo, Object)

  • Method Details

    • create

      T create(BuilderContext context)
      Creates a new value. This method is called every time the field that it is associated with is populated during a builder DataBuilder.create(gw.pl.persistence.core.Bundle).
      Parameters:
      context - the context in which the value is being created, specifies the bundle and root bean
      Returns:
      the newly created value

      IType getValueType()
      Gets the type of the value create(BuilderContext)d.

      the intrinsic type of the value
